user_prompt_template:
source_lang={source_lang}
target_lang={target_lang}
document_title={document_title}
source_url={source_url}
content_type=transcript_dialogue
learning_mode={learning_mode}
difficulty={difficulty}
cloze_max_sentences={cloze_max_sentences}
cloze_min_chars={cloze_min_chars}
cloze_max_per_chunk={cloze_max_per_chunk}

Learner profile:
- CEFR C1/C2; strong reading/listening comprehension but weaker natural spoken output in advanced contexts.
- Goal: convert passive comprehension into active, reusable expression.

Input format:
You will receive one or more chunks in this form:
chunk_id=<input chunk id, e.g., chunk_0001>
chunk_text=
<English transcript text>

Task:
Extract high-value, transfer-ready expressions for Anki cloze cards from transcript/dialogue text. Prioritize:
1) metaphorical or imagery-rich phrasing;
2) stance, concession/contrast, and discourse-organizer expressions;
3) abstraction or summarizing bridge expressions;
4) reusable high-frequency chunks, including phrasal verbs and strong collocations.

Selection gate (apply BEFORE output):
For each candidate, keep it only if all are true:
- text has 1..{cloze_max_sentences} sentences;
- text length >= {cloze_min_chars};
- each cloze span MUST be phrase-level (2-6 words), MUST not be a full sentence or full clause;
- candidate has 1-2 clozes (3 only when all spans are tightly related and high value).
If any rule fails, do not output that candidate.

Output:
Return a JSON array. Each item must contain at least:
{
  "chunk_id": "must exactly match one input chunk_id",
  "text": "1..{cloze_max_sentences} sentences and contains at least one cloze",
  "original": "matching source sentence(s), with no cloze markers and no HTML",
  "target_phrases": ["phrase1", "phrase2"],
  "note_hint": "optional short note"
}

Advanced-required fields:
- "phrase_types": 1-2 labels, strictly using the taxonomy defined in system prompt.
- "expression_transfer": <=120 chars, transfer-oriented usage hint, NOT a translation.

Hard constraints:
1) Cloze format must be {{cN::<b>...</b>}}(target-language translation). N increments by order of appearance within each text.
2) The parenthesized part after each cloze must be a concise translation of that cloze span in {target_lang}, not a generic hint.
3) Target 0..{cloze_max_per_chunk} high-quality candidates per chunk. 0 is allowed when nothing is suitable.
4) Avoid low-value targets: shallow function-word fragments, filler-only fragments, and trivial chunks.

If nothing is suitable, return an empty JSON array.

chunk_text:
{chunk_text}
